1. How to check if git is available on your system?
A) If we install it and then open the git we can say that git is available in our syatem and by using the commands like 
git help //and
git version //
we can verify weather git is correctly installed and running in our system.
2. How to initialize a new Git repository?
A) We can use the command git init to initialize the reposatory in Git.
3. How to tell git about your name and email?
A) We can use command
git congig --global user.name "username" for username;
git config --global user.email "email" for email.
4. How to add a file to the staging area?
A) we can use the command 
git add . or
git add <filename>. to add files to the staging area. 
5. How to remove a file from the staging area?
A) we can use the command 
git rm --Cached <filename> to remove the file from the stagging area. 
6. How to make a commit?
A) we can use the command 
git commit -m "//comment" <filename>. now the file is added to the local repository
7. How to send your changes to a remote repository?
A)we can use the command if we are in local 
git branch -M main  //for storing in main branch.
git remote add origin <url>
git push -u origin main.
If we are already in main we can use only this command
git push -u origin main.
by this we can 
8. What is the difference between clone and pull?
A) By the help of the clone we can download the files of the entire project into the local system.
   By the help of the pull we can download latest modified things in the respective modified files.    
